ANC President, Cyril Ramaphosa, will appeal to voters one last time at his party’s final election rally before Wednesday’s poll. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG – The ANC hopes to attract over 100, 000 supporters to the Siyanqoba rally before the 2019 election, that is according to Gauteng ANC chairperson David Makhura. ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa will appeal to voters one last time at his party's final election rally at Johannesburg's Ellis Park Stadium before Wednesday's poll. “Today will be very easy for us to fill the precinct, not just the Ellis Park Stadium but the precinct which includes the Johannesburg Stadium and the areas around it,” said Makhura. “We will have more than 100, 000 people. We have 1,800 busses picking up people for this very important rally.” ANC President, Cyril Ramaphosa, will appeal to voters one last time at his party’s final election rally before Wednesday’s poll. Courtesy #DStv403